                <shortdescription>input data values into lists.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 
<p> Press the [STAT] button and arrow twice to the right to the TESTS menu and select option <term> F: ANOVA( </term> and identify the four lists for the data. Press the [2nd] button [1] for L1 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [2] for L2 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [3] for L3 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [4] for L4 and  then [ )] button, then press [ENTER] to compute the test. </p>   
   
<figure xml:id=" TornadoData2">
            <caption>ANOVA test for Tornado Data</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAtorn2.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>On TI83 select F ANOVA and identify location of data as L1,L2,L3,L4.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 
   

<figure xml:id="TornadoData3">
            <caption>ANOVA Tornado Results</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAtorn3.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>F-test is 25.27 and p-value=.0002.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 

<p> The display lets you know you performed the one-way ANOVA. The test statistic is <m>F=934.21</m> and value of <m>p=0 </m>. The values under Factor are the between the data with SSB=29147.35 and MSB=9715.783. Using the arrow button down the Error is the Within data so SSW=166.4 and MSW=10.40. </p>
 </solution> 
<solution> <title> Tornadoes with TI-84</title> 
<p> <term> Input </term> the data for each method in a different List. Press the [STAT] button and under the EDIT menu select <term> 1:1 Edit</term>.  </p>
  
<figure xml:id="TornadoData4">
            <caption>Input Tornado Data</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAtorn4.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>input data values into lists.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 
<p> Press the [STAT] button and arrow twice to the right to the TESTS menu and select option <term> H: ANOVA( </term> and [ENTER] button and then identify the three lists for the data. Press the [2nd] button [1] for L1 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [2] for L2 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [3] for L3 then [ )] button, then press [ENTER] to compute the test. </p>   
  
<figure xml:id=" TornadoData5">
            <caption>ANOVA test for Tornado Data</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAtorn5.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>On TI84 select H ANOVA and identify location of data as L1,L2,L3,L4.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 
      
    
<figure xml:id="TornadoData6">
            <caption>ANOVA Tornado Results</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAtorn6.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>F-test is 934.2 and p-value=0.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 
<p> The display lets you know you performed the one-way ANOVA. The test statistic is <m>F=934.21</m> and value of <m>p=0 </m>. The values under Factor are the between the data with SSB=29147.35 and MSB=9715.783. Using the arrow button down the Error is the Within data so SSW=166.4 and MSW=10.40. </p>
</solution>

<solution> <title> Conclusion</title>
    <p>
      Since <m>p \lt 0.05</m>, we reject <m>H_0</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
      There is sufficient evidence at the <m>0.05</m> significance level to conclude that at least one mean annual tornado count differs among Colorado, Oklahoma, Texas, and Missouri. The obvious choice is that Texas has more tornadoes than the other states.
    </p>
  </solution>
</example> 

</subsection>




<subsection xml:id="subsec-ANOVAPractice">
  <title> ANOVA Practice Problems </title>
<p> For each problem, state the hypotheses, compute the test statistic, find the p-value, and state the conclusion in context. </p> 

<p> <term> Seedlings</term> </p>
    <p>
      A life scientist wants to compare the mean plant growth of bean seedlings
      grown under three different fertilizer treatments. A random sample of
      seedlings is assigned to each treatment, and after four weeks the growth
      of each plant, in centimeters, is recorded.
    </p>
    <table>
      <title>Plant Growth under Three Fertilizer Treatments</title>
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>Fertilizer A</cell>
          <cell>Fertilizer B</cell>
          <cell>Fertilizer C</cell>
        </row>
        <row><cell>12</cell><cell>15</cell><cell>18</cell></row>
        <row><cell>14</cell><cell>16</cell><cell>17</cell></row>
        <row><cell>13</cell><cell>14</cell><cell>19</cell></row>
        <row><cell>15</cell><cell>17</cell><cell>20</cell></row>
        <row><cell>11</cell><cell>15</cell><cell>18</cell></row>
      </tabular>
    </table>
    <p>
      At the <m>0.05</m> significance level, test whether the mean plant growth
      is the same for the three fertilizer treatments.
    </p>
<exercise xml:id="ex-anova-seedlings">
<title> Seedlings</title> 
  <statement>
<p>State the hypotheses, compute the means, test statistic and p-value with technology, and state the conclusion in context.</p>
  </statement>
  <solution> <title> Hypotheses</title> 
    <p>
      This is a one-way ANOVA test comparing three means.
    </p>
    <p>
      The hypotheses are
      <m>H_0:\mu_A=\mu_B=\mu_C</m> </p>
  <p> <m>H_a:</m> at least one population mean differs.
    </p>
</solution>
<solution> <title> Computations</title>
   <p>  First compute the sample means and standard deviations:</p>
   <p><m>\bar{x}_A=13</m> and <m> x_A = 1.58</m> </p>
   <p> <m>\bar{x}_B=15.4</m> and <m> x_B = 1.14</m> </p>
  <p>  <m>\bar{x}_C=18.4</m> and <m> x_C = 1.14</m> </p>
<p>  The grand mean is  <m>\bar{X}_{GM}=15.6</m>.
    </p>
    <p> The sum of squares between groups is</p>
<p> <m>  SSB=n\sum(\bar{x}_i-\bar{x})^2 </m></p>
   <p> <m>    SSB=5(13-15.6)^2+5(15.4-15.6)^2+5(18.4-15.6)^2 =73.2.  </m>  </p>
    <p>

      The sum of squares within groups is
      <m>SSW=10+5.2+5.2=20.4</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The total sum of squares is
      <m>SST=SSB+SSW=73.2+20.4=93.6</m>.
    </p>
    <table>
      <title>ANOVA Table</title>
      <tabular>
        <row>
          <cell>Source</cell>
          <cell>Sum of Squares</cell>
          <cell>Degrees of Freedom</cell>
          <cell>Mean Square</cell>
          <cell><m>F</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell>Between Groups</cell>
          <cell><m>73.2</m></cell>
          <cell><m>2</m></cell>
          <cell><m>36.6</m></cell>
          <cell><m>21.53</m></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell>Within Groups</cell>
          <cell><m>20.4</m></cell>
          <cell><m>12</m></cell>
          <cell><m>1.7</m></cell>
          <cell></cell>
        </row>
        <row>
          <cell>Total</cell>
          <cell><m>93.6</m></cell>
          <cell><m>14</m></cell>
          <cell></cell>
          <cell></cell>
        </row>
      </tabular>
    </table>
    <p>
      The test statistic is
      <m>F=\dfrac{MSB}{MSW}=\dfrac{36.6}{1.7}\approx 21.53</m>.
    </p>
    <p>
      The <m>p</m>-value for an <m>F</m>-distribution with
      <m>dfN=2</m> and <m>dfD=12</m> is <m>p=0.00011</m>.
    </p>
</solution>
<solution> <title> Seedlings with TI-84</title> 
<p> <term> Input </term> the data for each method in a different List. Press the [STAT] button and under the EDIT menu select <term> 1:1 Edit</term>.  </p>

  
<figure xml:id=" SeedlingData">
            <caption>ANOVA test for Seedling Data</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAseed1.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>On TI84 select H ANOVA and identify location of data as L1,L2,L3.</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 

<p> Press the [STAT] button and arrow twice to the right to the TESTS menu and select option <term> H: ANOVA( </term> and [ENTER] button and then identify the three lists for the data. Press the [2nd] button [1] for L1 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [2] for L2 then [,] button  and [2nd] button [3] for L3 then [ )] button, then press [ENTER] to compute the test. </p>    
    
<figure xml:id="SeedlingTest">
            <caption>ANOVA Seedling Results</caption>
            <image source="ANOVAseed2.png" width="90%">
                <shortdescription>F-test is 21.53 and p-value=0.00011</shortdescription>
            </image>
        </figure> 
<p> The display lets you know you performed the one-way ANOVA. The test statistic is <m>F=21.529</m> and value of <m>p=0.000107 </m>. The values under Factor are the between the data with SSB=73.2 and MSB=36.6. Using the arrow button down the Error is the Within data so SSW=20.4 and MSW=1.7 </p>
</solution>

<solution> <title> Conclusion</title>
    <p>  Since <m>p \lt0.05</m>, we reject <m>H_0</m>.    </p>
    <p>
      There is sufficient evidence at the <m>0.05</m> significance level to
      conclude that at least one mean plant growth differs among the three
      fertilizer treatments.
    </p>
  </solution>
</exercise>





